message.content: cs.SD, cs.SD is the most likely sub-category as the paper deals with speech and audio technology. Other likely sub-categories could be cs.CL (computational linguistics) as the paper deals with phone classification, cs.LG (machine learning) as the paper proposes two novel unsupervised approaches, cs.SI (sound and music computing) as the paper deals with acoustic embeddings, and cs.CV (computer vision and pattern recognition) as the paper deals with encoding and decoding of audio frames.
